This paper deals with computational complexity in the context of abstract argumentation, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problems studied involve modifying and aggregating sets of arguments, which are common tasks in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG and cs.DM). The paper also uses parameterized complexity, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science that deals with analyzing algorithms with respect to a specific parameter (cs.DS and cs.CC).
